游戏初期的可选关卡“No Russian”中，玩家将控制潛伏行動(Deep Cover Operation)的[[中央情报局|中央情报局]]特工和前陆军游骑兵约瑟夫·艾伦，与一队俄罗斯极端民族主义恐怖分子在机场制造大屠杀。关卡名来源于恐怖分子头目弗拉基米尔·马卡洛夫，他告诉玩家和其他枪手在整个场景中的指示“记住，不准說俄语”。受惊的平民尖叫着四散逃离，在地上爬行的伤者拖出斑斑血迹，还有一些人尝试把人拖到安全地带，却无法逃脱被杀的命运。尽管玩家在技术上跟恐怖分子结盟，但可以不用杀死任何平民来履行任务目标。玩家不能杀死其他恐怖分子，这会导致任务失败<ref name="MW2">{{cite video game|title=Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2|developer=[[Infinity_Ward|Infinity Ward]]|date=2009-11-14|publisher=[[Activision|Activision]]|level="No Russian"|platform=[[PlayStation_3|PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox_360|Xbox 360]], [[Microsoft_Windows|Microsoft Windows]]}}</ref>。

任务开始前，玩家会被警告任务“含有令人不安的内容”，可以选择跳过关卡而不受惩罚。如果玩家不提前跳过任务，仍然可以在关卡的任何时刻跳过。玩家跳过关卡不会受到处罚，杀害平民或机场安检人员没有分数。同样，执行任务不会赢得具体的成就或勋章。但需要击退停机坪上的FSB士兵。在关卡的结尾，马卡洛夫识破了艾伦的真实身份，他杀害了艾伦随即逃跑。当美国特工尸体被发现时，俄罗斯政府误以为是美国策划对该国的入侵<ref name="MW2"/><ref name="warning">{{cite video game|title=Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2|developer=[[Infinity_Ward|Infinity Ward]]|date=2009-11-14|publisher=[[Activision|Activision]]|platform=[[PlayStation_3|PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox_360|Xbox 360]], [[Microsoft_Windows|Microsoft Windows]]|quote='''Disturbing Warning Notice''': Some players may find one of the missions disturbing or offensive. Would you like to have the option to skip this mission? (You will not be penalized in terms of [[PlayStation_Network#Trophies|Trophies]]/[[Xbox_Live#Gamerscore|Achievements]] or game completion.)}}</ref>。

===各国反应===
====俄罗斯====
该任务在俄罗斯PC版中被删除。最初报道，由于俄罗斯游戏机版被召回，导致销售被推迟。但Activision表示此报告是假的，它早已决定在PC版中删掉“No Russian”任务。由于俄罗斯没有正式的分级委员会，在与当地律师交谈之后作出决定。俄罗斯联邦内的另一个游戏评级机构“电视和电影分级委员会”（CRRS）不愿发表意见。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://features.csmonitor.com/innovation/2009/11/17/modern-warfare-2-not-banned-in-russia-according-to-activision|title=Modern Warfare 2 not banned in Russia, according to Activision|date=2009-11-17|accessdate=2009-11-17|archive-date=2009-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091122133703/http://features.csmonitor.com/innovation/2009/11/17/modern-warfare-2-not-banned-in-russia-according-to-activision/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamerzines.com/xbox-360/news/modern-warfare-2-russia-banned.html |title=Modern Warfare 2 Russia Banned, XBox 360 News — GamerZines : Free Digital Games Magazines |publisher=GamerZines |date= |accessdate=2009-11-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091119034651/http://www.gamerzines.com/xbox-360/news/modern-warfare-2-russia-banned.html |archivedate=2009-11-19 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Listed in: PlayStation 3, Xbox 360, Games for Windows |url=http://www.qj.net/Russians-ban-Modern-Warfare-2-console-versions-for-No-Russian-mission/pg/49/aid/135926 |title=Russians ban Modern Warfare 2 console versions for 'No Russian' mission — PC Gaming, PlayStation, Wii, Nintendo DS, Xbox 360, News, Reviews, Downloads, Custom Apps, Homebrew and much more |publisher=Qj.net |date=2009-11-01 |accessdate=2009-11-16 |archive-date=2011-07-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724024633/http://www.qj.net/Russians-ban-Modern-Warfare-2-console-versions-for-No-Russian-mission/pg/49/aid/135926 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.neoseeker.com/forums/41612/t1448614-russians-ban-modern-warfare-2-console-versions-for-no-russian-mission/ |title=Russians ban Modern Warfare 2 console versions for 'No Russian' mission — Neoseeker Forums |publisher=Neoseeker.com |date= |accessdate=2009-11-16 |archive-date=2009-11-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091119101437/http://www.neoseeker.com/forums/41612/t1448614-russians-ban-modern-warfare-2-console-versions-for-no-russian-mission/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://multiplayerblog.mtv.com/2009/11/17/activision-disputes-russian-modern-warfare-2-ban-claims/ |title=Activision Disputes Russian ‘Modern Warfare 2′ Ban Claims » MTV Multiplayer |publisher=Multiplayerblog.mtv.com |date=2009-11-17 |accessdate=2009-12-12 |archive-date=2015-09-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150913004727/http://multiplayerblog.mtv.com/2009/11/17/activision-disputes-russian-modern-warfare-2-ban-claims/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

